<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="354" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,188,213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Viraktamath &amp; Mohan" authorityName="Viraktamath &amp; Mohan" box="[584,948,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifidus">
<emphasis box="[584,688,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">S. bifidus</emphasis>
Viraktamath &amp; Mohan
</taxonomicName>
in external morphology and male genitalia, but can be distinguished by: aedeagal shaft gradually tapered apically and truncated at apex in lateral view, connective processes asymmetrically curved and with convoluted ridge in apical region.
</paragraph>
